# GNU Stow ignore — controls what is NOT symlinked into $HOME.
# Stow's job: keep repo-internal, non-dotfile paths out of the stow target.
#
# Runtime/secret state is git's concern (see .gitignore), NOT stow's: dirs like
# .claude, .agents and .config/opencode are stowed as a single folded symlink,
# so stow never descends into their runtime subdirs — enumerating them here
# would be inert. That is why this list is short and does not mirror .gitignore.
#
# NOTE: a custom .stow-local-ignore replaces Stow's built-in defaults, so the
# VCS/metadata entries below must be listed explicitly.

# VCS, stow and editor project metadata (repo-only, not home dotfiles)
\.git
\.gitignore
\.stow-local-ignore
\.DS_Store
\.vscode

# Repo docs and tooling
README\.md
LICENSE\.md
Makefile
AGENTS\.md

# Shell phase source trees — sourced via $DOTFILES, never symlinked into $HOME
zshenv
zshrc
zprofile
completions

# Local-only / app-managed paths (not meant to live in $HOME)
# raycast: point Raycast's script-command directory at $DOTFILES/raycast instead
# of symlinking it into $HOME.
\.navgator\.toml
\.ruff_cache
swiftbar
raycast
